## Tech Stack
- **Backend**: Python 3.12, FastAPI, SQLAlchemy 2 (async + asyncpg), Alembic, Pydantic v2, scapy
- **Database**: PostgreSQL 16
- **Frontend**: React 18, TypeScript, Vite, Tailwind CSS, TanStack Query, TanStack Virtual
- **Auth**: GitHub OAuth via authlib + JWT cookie (`pcap_session`) using python-jose; login is gated by the `allowed_users` allowlist and `User.role`
- **LLM**: OpenAI SDK (configurable base_url for any compatible API)
- **Infra**: Docker Compose, Nginx

## Deployment Modes
| Mode | Compose File | Containers | Base Images |
|------|-------------|-----------|-------------|
| **Production (1Panel)** | `docker-compose.yml` | 1 (web) | Pre-built image from Harbor (`img.aksg.net/pcapgo/pcapgo`) |
| **Testing / Dev** | `tests/docker-compose.yml` | 3 (postgres + web + nginx) | `postgres:16-alpine`, internal Node/Python/nginx images |

Production mode pulls the pre-built Harbor image, which bundles the React SPA into the Python image. The backend serves the frontend via `StaticFiles` when `SERVE_FRONTEND=true`. The container joins 1Panel's existing `1panel-network` so it can reach 1Panel-managed PostgreSQL and the 1Panel reverse proxy.

> **Sample vs. live deployment:** `docker-compose.yml` and `.env.sample` in this repo are **sample templates**. The live deployment lives in a separate directory on the host (e.g. `~/pcapgo-deploy/`) holding copies named `docker-compose.yml` + `.env` with real secrets; the repo stays free of production secrets. The deploy compose pulls the pre-built Harbor image by default; uncomment the `build:` block to build locally from this repo instead.

> **Image publishing:** building, tagging (`img.aksg.net/pcapgo/pcapgo:<version>` + `:latest`), pushing to Harbor, key-based cosign signing, and Trivy vulnerability scanning / CVE allowlisting are all documented in `release.mdc`. Versions are git-tag-driven (`v0.0.1` → GitHub tag + Harbor `0.0.1` + `latest`). Always build with `--pull` so base images are refreshed to latest on every build.

## Database
- Engine: `postgresql+asyncpg`
- Session: `async_sessionmaker` with `expire_on_commit=False`
- Models: `User` (role: user/super_admin), `AllowedUser` (case-insensitive GitHub login allowlist), `Capture` (status enum: uploaded/parsing/ready/failed), `Conversation`, `Analysis`, `ChatThread`, `ChatMessage`
- Migrations: Alembic in `backend/alembic/` (0001 initial, 0002 chat threads, 0003 user management)

## Key Conventions
- All Python files start with `from __future__ import annotations`.
- All API routes return Pydantic response models except the SSE endpoints: `/api/captures/{id}/ai` (full analysis), `/api/captures/{id}/threads/{tid}/messages` (chat), `/api/captures/{id}/explain` (one-shot packet explanation), and `/api/capture-command/generate` (tcpdump/pktmon command generation) — all `StreamingResponse` with `media_type="text/event-stream"`.
- Uploads are streamed to a temp file, validated by pcap magic bytes, then atomically renamed to `uploads/<user_id>/<capture_id>.pcap`.
- Parsing runs as a FastAPI `BackgroundTask` and is offloaded to a worker thread with `asyncio.to_thread`. It writes four sidecars: `.jsonl`, `.summary.jsonl`, `.offsets.bin` (binary offset pairs), `.index.json`.
- Captures never expose `/uploads/` via StaticFiles or nginx; files are served only through authenticated API routes.
- Auth is cookie-based via `pcap_session` containing a JWT (configurable lifetime via `JWT_EXPIRE_MINUTES`). Every authenticated request re-checks `allowed_users`; removing a login from the allowlist revokes existing sessions on the next request, and role changes sync into `users.role`.
- `ADMIN_GITHUB_USER` seeds/restores an undeletable `super_admin` allowlist entry on startup and repairs any matching existing `users.role`.
- Every capture-scoped endpoint enforces ownership for normal users (`Capture.user_id == user.id`); `super_admin` users can access all captures through shared `get_capture_for_user`. `GET /api/captures?all=true&owner=<github_login>` lists all captures with optional owner filtering.
- Follow Stream and the proto/`q` packet filter re-read sidecars / the pcap in worker threads (`asyncio.to_thread`) so large reads never block the event loop.
- `DATABASE_URL` controls the DB connection.
- Settings are loaded via Pydantic `BaseSettings` with `.env` file support and `extra="ignore"`.

## How to Run
```bash
# Production (1Panel) — single container, from a host deploy dir.
# Samples (docker-compose.yml, .env.sample) are copied from this repo into
# the deploy dir as docker-compose.yml + .env.
cd ~/pcapgo-deploy && docker compose up -d

# Testing / Dev — full 3-container stack
docker compose -f tests/docker-compose.yml up -d

# Development backend (no Docker)
cd backend && pip install -r requirements.txt && uvicorn app.main:app --reload --port 8000

# Development frontend (no Docker)
cd frontend && npm install && npm run dev
```

## How to Test
```bash
# All backend tests (requires PostgreSQL on localhost:5432 with pcap_test)
cd backend && python -m pytest -v

# Backend unit tests only
cd backend && python -m pytest -c pytest.ini ../tests/backend/unit/ -v

# Backend API integration tests only
cd backend && python -m pytest -c pytest.ini ../tests/backend/api/ -v

# All frontend tests (vitest + jsdom, no backend needed)
cd frontend && npx vitest run

# Frontend tests in watch mode
cd frontend && npx vitest

# Frontend TypeScript checks
cd frontend && npm run typecheck
cd frontend && npm run typecheck:test
```
Test DB: `postgresql+asyncpg://pcap:pcap@localhost:5432/pcap_test`

### Test Coverage Summary
- **Backend**: 348 tests (unit + integration + migrations) — requires PostgreSQL
- **Frontend**: 18 test files (278 tests) — self-contained, no server needed
- **Test frameworks**: pytest + pytest-asyncio (backend), vitest + @testing-library/react (frontend)

## Environment Variables
Required: `DATABASE_URL`, `GITHUB_CLIENT_ID`, `GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET`, `GITHUB_OAUTH_REDIRECT_URL`, `JWT_SECRET`, `PUBLIC_BASE_URL`, `ADMIN_GITHUB_USER`
Optional: `LLM_API_KEY`, `LLM_BASE_URL`, `LLM_MODEL`, `MAX_UPLOAD_MB`, `COOKIE_SECURE`, `SESSION_SECRET`, `DEV_MODE`, `JWT_EXPIRE_MINUTES`
Compose-only: `SERVE_FRONTEND`, `WEB_PORT`, `NGINX_PORT`, `POSTGRES_PASSWORD`
